## Part 7: What We Say vs. What We Don't Say

### Always say:
- "Deterministic" (our enforcement can't be bypassed by the LLM)
- "One line of code" (our integration story)
- "Under 10ms" (our performance claim)
- "Every tool call" (our coverage claim)
- Specific attack scenarios with real details
- Specific dollar amounts for cost savings
- Framework names (LangChain, CrewAI, AutoGen, Vercel AI)

### Never say:
- "AI-powered" (we're the opposite — we're deterministic, not AI)
- "Comprehensive solution" (vague corporate language)
- "Best-in-class" (unsubstantiated claim)
- "Leverage" (as a verb — corporate buzzword)
- "End-to-end" (meaningless)
- "Cutting-edge" (says nothing)
- "Digital transformation" (instant credibility loss)
- "We help organizations" (passive, boring, corporate)

